    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nFrom v0.5.1 to HEAD\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nArch Linux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.25.0\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nany\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n1. Run `nvim --clean`\r\n2. Type `:lua vim.api.nvim_set_keymap('', 'foo', '\\0', {})` or `:lua vim.api.nvim_replace_termcodes('\\000', true, true, true)` and press Enter\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNo hang\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nNvim hangs with increasing CPU usage.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
